commit 3198e00929b88d95c078def62925e9811ccce782
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 10:55:28 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(list-edit): admin add/remove/reorder UI + list-op action via DraftEditor

    Sub-commit 2.3 of registration-launch Branch 2 (ADR 0006, settled #10).

    The /admin editor gains per-list Add / Remove / move-up/down controls and a
    new `intent=list-op` action that parses `list:<path>:<kind>` control fields
    (`collectListOps`, 2.2) and applies them through a new
    `DraftEditor.applyListOps` — the id-keyed structural edit (`applyListEdit`, 2.2)
    auto-saved to the draft, mirroring `applyImageUpload` (the route stays thin; the
    bucket-key choreography never leaks back). Calling `applyListOps` rather than
    `editDocument(scope, merged)` is deliberate: `editDocument`'s array-by-index
    `deepMerge` is wrong for remove/reorder (that branch dies in 2.4).

    "Add" appends an item carrying only its `id` (settled #10) so a later photo
    upload / field edit has a server-side target. The strict `SiteContent` `Text`
    invariant would reject that stub on save, but ADR 0006 is explicit: an
    incomplete required field blocks PUBLISH, not draft save. So this introduces a
    `DraftSiteContent` schema — a draft is content-lax DOWN TO THE LEAF (per-locale
    optional `DraftText`, optional `DraftImageRef.alt`, optional `position`) while
    identity / asset / enum leaves stay strict WHEN PRESENT (only absence/emptiness
    is tolerated, never a malformed value). `DraftEditor` draft read/store decode
    `DraftSiteContent`; `publish` re-decodes the strict `SiteContent`, the single
    boundary that enforces the both-locales invariant (an incomplete item is
    rejected with a 400). `AdminContent.content` is now the draft shape; the view
    renders partial items with empty defaults.

    List items also gain a unique-`id` invariant (`uniqueListItemIds`, applied to
    speakers/seminars/team in both the strict and draft documents) so the id-keyed
    merge/reorder can never be made ambiguous by a duplicate id.

    Field-name templates stay positional (id-keyed names are 2.4).

    Tests: list-op add/remove/reorder e2e through `applyListOps`; add→untouched
    save-draft succeeds; add→image-upload (no alt yet) succeeds; add is
    publish-invalid; `DraftSiteContent` draft-lax/publish-strict + malformed-leaf
    rejection + unique-id rejection.

    Gate: typecheck + lint + build + 226 tests green. Codex-reviewed (3 findings
    fixed: draft-save regression, add→upload completion, duplicate-id reorder).

